{"parse":{"title":"Bed-making","pageid":36251829,"revid":799633480,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg/220px-Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg/330px-Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg/440px-Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2592\" data-file-height=\"1944\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bed_in_Seattle_hotel.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>An unmade hotel bed.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Bed-making</b> is the act of arranging the <a href=\"/wiki/Bed_sheet\" title=\"Bed sheet\">bedsheets</a> and other <a href=\"/wiki/Bedding\" title=\"Bedding\">bedding</a> on a <a href=\"/wiki/Bed\" title=\"Bed\">bed</a>, to prepare it for use.<sup id=\"cite_ref-oed_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-oed-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It is a household chore, but is also performed in establishments including hospitals, hotels, and military or educational residences. Bed-making is also a common childhood chore.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bed-making&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Beds must sometimes be made to exacting standards, demanded of nurses or military personnel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In a <a href=\"/wiki/Hospital\" title=\"Hospital\">hospital</a> or other health-care environment, beds must sometimes be made while occupied by a patient. Specialised techniques are taught to healthcare staff to enable beds to be made efficiently with due care for the patient.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>There are different bed-making techniques, such as \"hospital corners\" and \"mitred corners\". <a href=\"/wiki/Military_recruit\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Military recruit\">Military recruits</a> are often taught how to make a neat and tidy bed with hospital corners. Military personnel are expected to fold the bed very tightly, in some cases so that a coin can bounce off of it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Since 2012, many <a href=\"/wiki/Self-making_bed\" title=\"Self-making bed\">self-making beds</a> which automatically rearrange the bedding are in development and in use.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> New innovations in bedding have arisen in recent years (beginning in 2014<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>) that have further simplified bed-making\u2014some claiming that zipper beds can be made in under 10 seconds.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Record\">Record</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bed-making&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Record\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Guinness_World_Records\" title=\"Guinness World Records\">Guinness World Records</a> reports that the record time for two people to make a bed \"with one blanket, two sheets, an undersheet, an uncased pillow, one pillowcase, one counterpane and hospital corners\" is 14.0 seconds. This feat was achieved by two nurses from the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Masonic_Hospital\" title=\"Royal Masonic Hospital\">Royal Masonic Hospital</a> in London in 1993.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bed-making&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-oed-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-oed_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">\"Make (v. 1): 62:\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/112645?rskey=tyGmtC&amp;result=9&amp;isAdvanced=false#\"><i>Oxford English Dictionary</i></a>. <span style=\"font-size:90%; color:#555\">(Subscription required (<span title=\"The site requires a paid subscription to access this page.\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted;cursor:help\">help</span>))</span>. <q>To prepare (a bed) for sleeping in; to arrange bedclothes on (a bed) for future use.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Make+%28v.+1%29%3A+62%3A&amp;rft.btitle=Oxford+English+Dictionary&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.oed.com%2Fview%2FEntry%2F112645%3Frskey%3DtyGmtC%26result%3D9%26isAdvanced%3Dfalse%23&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABed-making\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-ci